{
  "texts": [
    "A cubic water box with an edge distance of 13Å encapsulated the system, supplemented by a 0.15 M ionic NaCl solution for solvation neutralization.",
    "Gromacs software version 2021 85, operationalized on the Dutch supercomputer Snellius, facilitated all simulations.",
    "The energy minimization of solvated systems involved a sequence of steps utilizing the steepest descent method and the conjugate gradient algorithm.",
    "Subsequently, equilibration occurred through 5 ns NPT (constant Number of atoms, Pressure, Temperature) ensemble after the first 1 ns NVT (constant Number of atoms, Volume, Temperature) ensemble.",
    "Binding free energy calculation."
  ]
}